cs.LG, cs.ST, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.NA

Reasoning: 
1) cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an algorithm for finding the best linear model to minimize least-squares loss given a data-set. This is a fundamental problem in machine learning and falls under the scope of cs.LG.
2) cs.ST (Statistics): The paper establishes data-dependent estimation error bounds for the proposed algorithm, which is a statistical analysis. Hence, it can be categorized under cs.ST.
3) cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper analyzes the convergence rate of the proposed algorithm, which involves information-theoretic concepts such as sub-exponential distributions. Hence, it can be categorized under cs.IT.
4) cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new algorithm for solving a fundamental problem in machine learning, which involves designing efficient algorithms. Hence, it can be categorized under cs.DS.
5) cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper proposes a numerical algorithm (projected gradient descent) for solving the optimization problem, which involves numerical analysis. Hence, it can be categorized under cs.NA.
